AMENDMENT V

 
 ARTICLE II - MEMBERSHIP, shall be amended in its entirety to read 
as follows:

Section 1. Membership with the Fort Bidwell Indian Community 
shall consist of those persons who qualify under one of the 
following categories:

(a)  All persons of the community whose names appear on 
the Official Census Roll, dated April 1, 1934.

(b)  All children born between April 1, 1934, and the 

effective date of this amendment to any member of 
the community.

(c)  All children of one-fourth (1/4) or more degree of 

Indian blood born on or after the effective date of 
this amendment to members of the Fort Bidwell Indian 

 Community.

(d)  Admission to membership through adoption shall be 
governed by an ordinance enacted by the governing 
body and approved by the Secretary of the Interior.

Sec. 2. If a person who meets the above eligibility require
ments has been allotted on another reservation or public 

 domain land or is a recognized member of another tribe, band, 
or group of Indians or has relinquished membership in the 
Fort Bidwell Indian Community, such person shall be disquali
fied for membership. However, an allotment or an interest in 
 an allotment acquired through will, gift, deed, or inheritance 

shall not be a bar to membership. A "recognized member of 
some other tribe, band or group" is a person who has been 
listed on a membership roll, received a land use assignment, 
or otherwise shared in the benefits accorded to the Indians 
of another reservation.

Sec. 3. The governing body shall adopt an enrollment ordinance 
subject to the approval of the Secretary of the Interior, 
prescribing rules and procedures by which the initial member
ship roll shall be prepared and thereafter kept current. Any 
person denied membership shall have the right of appeal to 
the Secretary of the Interior pursuant to 25 CFR, Part 42.

Sec. 4. Corrections may be made to the roll at any time by 
the Fort Bidwell Community Council, subject to approval by 
the Secretary of the Interior.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Acting Deputy Associate 

Commissioner of Indian Affairs on February 4, 1971, under 

delegated authority, the attached Amendment No. V to the Constitution 

and Bylaws of the Fort Bidwell Indian Community of the Fort Bidwell 

Reservation of California was submitted to the qualified voters of 

the community and was on May 22, 1971, 

duly adopted

by a vote of 27 for, and 0 against, in an election in 

which at least 30 percent of the 34 members entitled to vote

cast their ballots in accordance with Section 16 of the Indian

Reorganization Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended by 

the Act of June 15, 1935 (49 Stat. 378).
 
  
  
  
 

