AMENDMENT VI

 
 ARTICLE III - GOVERNING BODY, Section 3 of the constitution, the 
first sentence shall be amended to read:

The Fort Bidwell Indian Community Council, so elected, shall 
elect from its own membership a chairman, vice-chairman, 
secretary and a treasurer,

ARTICLE III - GOVERNING BODY, Section 6 of the constitution, shall 
be amended in its entirety to read: 
.

The chairman may, by written notice, call special meetings of 
the council or community. Upon petition, signed by not less 
than twenty-five percent (25%) of the eligible voters of the 
community, submitted to the chairman or secretary of the 
council, the chairman shall call a community meeting for the 
purpose of (a) voting to rescind enactments of the council, 
(b) voting to terminate actions of the council in the proposal 
stage, (c) voting on proposals by the community at large.
Such meetings shall be publicly noticed at least fifteen (15) 
days in advance of the meeting. To be officially recognized, 
such elections and meetings must be participated in by at 
least thirty percent (30%) of the eligible voters of the 
community.
 
 

