AMENDMENT VII

 
 ARTICLE IV - POWERS OF THE COMMUNITY COUNCIL, Section 1(d) of the 
constitution shall be amended in its entirety to read:

(d)  To manage all land, property, community enterprises, and 
economic affairs of the Fort Bidwell Indian Community in 
conformity with applicable law, including but not limited 
to the establishment of housing or rental authorities, 
loan programs, and approval of planning, programming and 
development projects of all community lands and assets.

ARTICLE IV, Section 1 of the constitution, shall be amended by 
adding a new subsection (e) to read as follows:

(e)  To appropriate community funds which are on deposit in 

the local treasury, and to use such funds for the benefit 
of the community, and to authorize the appropriation and 
use of community trust funds which are on deposit in the 
United States Treasury.

ARTICLE IV, Section 4 of the constitution, shall be deleted in its 
entirety.

ARTICLE IV, Section 5 of the constitution shall now become Section 4 
and shall be amended to read as follows:

 Sec. 4. Any rights and powers vested in Paiute Indians of
 the Fort Bidwell Indian Community which are not expressly 
referred to in this article shall not be abridged by this 
article, but may be exercised by the community council 
through the enactment of appropriate constitutional amendments.

ARTICLE IV, Sections 6(a) and (b) shall be deleted.
 
 

