AMENDMENT X

 
 ARTICLE VIII - NOMINATIONS AND ELECTIONS, Section 3 of the 
constitution, shall be amended in its entirety to read:

Sec. 3. Any enrolled member of the Fort Bidwell Indian 
Community, who is twenty-one (21) years of age or over and is 
a legal resident of the reservation or is registered to 
vote, shall be entitled to vote. Registration and voting 
procedures, including absentee voting, shall be established 
by the council.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Acting Deputy Associate 

Commissioner of Indian Affairs on February 4, 197I, under 

delegated authority, the attached Amendment No. X to the Constitution 

and Bylaws of the Fort Bidwell Indian Community of the Fort Bidwell 

Reservation of California was submitted to the qualified voters of 

the community and was on May 22, 1971, duly adopted

