CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS 
 
 of the 
 
FORT BIDWELL INDIAN COMMUNITY 
 
 of the 
 
FORT BIDWELL RESERVATION 

 
  
 of 
 
CALIFORNIA

AMENDMENT XI

 
 ARTICLES I and V of the bylaws shall be amended by deleting from 
them "business committee" and substituting in lieu thereof "community 
council."

ARTICLE IV of the bylaws shall be amended by deleting the words 
"and of the business committee" in the first sentence.

ARTICLE IV of the bylaws shall be further amended by deleting the 
words "and its business committee" in the third sentence.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Acting Deputy Associate

Commissioner of Indian Affairs on February 4, 1971, under

delegated authority, the attached Amendment No. XI to the Constitution 

and Bylaws of the Fort Bidwell Indian Community of the Fort Bidwell 

Reservation of California was submitted to the qualified voters of 

the community and was on May 22, 1971, duly adopted

by a vote of 24 for, and 3 against, in an election in

which at least 30 percent of the 34 members entitled to 

vote cast their ballots in accordance with Section 16 of the Indian 

Reorganization Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), as amended by 

the Act of June 15, 1935 (49 Stat. 378).
 
  
  
  
 

CONSTITUTION AND BYLAWS 
 
 of the 
 
FORT BIDWELL INDIAN COMMUNITY 
 
 of the 
 
FORT BIDWELL RESERVATION 

 
  
 of 
 
CALIFORNIA

AMENDMENT XII

 
 A new Article shall be added to the constitution entitled, 
ARTICLE IX - RIGHTS OF MEMBERS, and shall read as follows:
 
 

ARTICLE IX - RIGHTS OF MEMBERS

 
 Section 1. The relevant protections guaranteed by Title II of 
the Civil Rights Act of 1968 (82 Stat, 77), against actions of 
a tribe in exercising its powers of self-government shall apply 
to the Fort Bidwell Indian Community.

Sec. 2. Community members shall have the right to review 
community records at any reasonable time in accordance with 
procedures established by the community council.
 
 

CERTIFICATE OF RESULTS OF ELECTION

 
 Pursuant to an election authorized by the Acting Deputy Associate 

Commissioner of Indian Affairs on February 4, 1971, under

delegated authority, the attached Amendment No- XII to the 

Constitution and Bylaws of the Fort Bidwell Indian Community of 

the Fort Bidwell Reservation of California was submitted to the 

qualified voters of the community and was on May 22
 
 

, 

 
 1971, duly adopted by a vote of 27 for, and 0 against,

in an election in which at least 30 percent of the 34 members 

entitled to vote cast their ballots in accordance with Section 16 

of the Indian Reorganization Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), 

as amended by the Act of June 15, 1935 (49 Stat.. 378).
 
 

 
APPROVAL

 
 I, Harrison Loesch, Assistant Secretary 

of the Interior of the United States of America, by virtue of the 

authority granted to me by the Act of June 18, 1934 (48 Stat. 984), 

as amended, do hereby approve the attached Amendments V, VI, VII, 

VIII, IX, X, XI, and XII to the Constitution and Bylaws of the 

Port Bidwell Indian Community of the Fort Bidwell Reservation of 

California.

Approval Recommended:

(Sgd) Ernest Stevens

Commissioner of Indian Affairs

